            <h3>Why?... How?... Really?... The True Story</h3>
            <p>
                Every year, the majority of us enjoy celebrating our birthdays in numerous ways. But honestly speaking,
                birthdays have
                become predictable and calculated if they happen every year.
                <br />
                <br />
                I miss giving true meaning to celebration-worthy events. For me, it has to be an event that is
                worthy enough of a celebration of a lifetime. An important milestone that is unique, special, one of
                a kind, and memorable. This is that event.
                <br />
                <br />
                One night about a year ago, I
                began thinking about my age in days. So quickly, I googled a date calculator and no surprise, I got
                a big number in the realms of 9,500!
                <br />
                <br />
                "Wow! That's so close to 10,000 days!" I thought, " So what would that day be...?",
                I quickly restructured the formula and my answer was
                revealed:
                <br />
                <br />
            </p>

            <div class="equation">
                <h2>TUESDAY, JUNE 4, 1996</h2>
                <h2> + </h2>
                <h2> 10,000 DAYS </h2>
                <h2> = </h2>
                <h2>SATURDAY, OCTOBER 21ST, 2023</h2>
            </div>
            <br />
            <p>
                As if fate already had me destined to celebrate this experience with great people (you) on a day no
                better
                than a Saturday, the weekend!
                <br />
                <br />
                I am so grateful that I have experienced
                10,000 mornings and evenings and can't wait to celebrate that with the very best of people to make it a
                night that puts all
                my
                previous
                birthday gatherings to shame. This will be a night to remember. And I hope you join me in such a special
                moment.
                <br />
                <br />
                I cannot wait to see you there!
            </p>
        </div>
